ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The course lays the foundation for understanding how to read the tables in sociological articles.
I would highly recommend this course and instructor to a fellow student.

This is a good introductory course to statistics, with a strong focus on teaching and class participation. I recommend it to anyone who is also open to group-learning and didactics over learning through books.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course has made me more literate in a language in which I was completely illiterate before taking the course.
The ability to read a regression table and understand the mechanics behind statistical regression is invaluable.
It contributed to solidify the foundation for my future research.
